FullTitle: American Express is now accepted at Boulangerie Asanoya
FullDescription:
Asanoya's started in 1933 Karuizawa Japan, as a store catering to foreign embassies and diplomats from various countries. The shop was very well-received and soon grew to be a favourite destination for the noble class. With the increased demand for European-type hard breads, Asanoya began to improve their baking skills, techniques and facilities, giving discerning customers the chance to eat truly fresh baked bread. 
 Through the years, Asanoya expanded their operations in many other Japanese cities. Eventually opening their famous outlet in Tokyo Midtown, where you can expect premium, high quality bread from well-kept recipes that have been consistent through the years. 
 With the opening of the first outlet outside of Japan, customers can truly experience and appreciate the wonderful and delectable products right here in Singapore. Asanoya•s freshly baked treats will never fail to delight.

FullTitle: American Express is now accepted at Power Up Express
FullDescription:
Power Up Express provides a variety of sports products, ranging from specialized 2XU compression and triathlon gear, stylish gym apparel to high performance running gear such as Brooks and Newton running shoes. 
 To complement one's training and sporting needs, Power Up Express also has a series of durable and light weighted Nathan hydration systems as well as other accessories for selection. They have their comfort range of Aetrex products, catering to people who are looking for comfort shoes as well as shoes that are able to fit orthotics. The iStepFoot Scanning Technology which quickly identifies one's arch type, and pressure points can also be found here. 
 Apart from the technical and trendy gear, athletes will also be delighted to know that Power Up Express offer sports massage services for those who need muscle conditioning or a speedier recovery from their races, right in the store. 
 Podiatry consultation is also available at the store by qualified Podiatrist, who may recommend customized orthotics and the right shoes for better footcare management.
